0. Definitions

a. “Software” means the MultiPixel game, engine, tools, launchers, assets,
   data, and all related components provided by MultiPixel.

b. “User” means any individual who lawfully obtains and uses the Software.

c. “Mod(s)” means any modification, plugin, add-on, or derivative work
   created by a User that is based on or interacts with the Software,
   including API-only Mods.

d. “Server” means any multiplayer, online, or networked instance that uses
   the Software, including unofficial or community-hosted servers.

e. “Gross revenue” means all monetary payments received before any deductions,
including donations, subscriptions, item sales, advertisements,
sponsorships, and cryptocurrency transactions that have a verifiable
market value at the time of the transaction. Non‑monetary barter or
informal exchanges are excluded unless their fair market value is
documented and recorded by the Server operator.

f. “Political Server” means any Server where political topics are a primary
   or significant focus.

g. “Private use” means use of the Software by an individual who has lawfully
obtained a license. Private use does not permit transferring, sharing,
uploading, sending, exchanging, or distributing the Software, its source
code, its binaries, or any modified or unmodified version of it to any
other person, including other licensed Users. Viewing or demonstrating the
Software to others is allowed, but all copies, builds, and code must remain
strictly private and may not be provided to any third party without
explicit written approval from MultiPixel.


1. Nature of License (No Ownership Transfer)

a. The Software is licensed, not sold. MultiPixel retains all rights, title,
   and interest in and to the Software.

b. MultiPixel grants the User a limited, personal, non-exclusive,
   non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable license to install and
   use the Software for personal, non-commercial purposes.

c. No rights are granted except those expressly stated in this License.

2. Grant of Rights

a. The User may:
   i. Install and run the Software for personal use.
   ii. View and study the source code where made available.
   iii. Modify the source code for personal, private use only.

b. The User may NOT:
   i. Copy, reuse, or reimplement any part of the Software.
   ii. Translate or port the Software to another language or engine.
   iii. Use the Software as reference for another game or engine.

3. Modding Permission

a. Users may create Mods for personal, private use.

b. No Mod, derivative work, or modified version of the Software may be
transferred to any other person, including other licensed Users, without
explicit written approval from MultiPixel.

c. All Mods, including API-only Mods, are considered derivative works of the
   Software to the fullest extent permitted by law. To the extent that any
   Mod is not classified as a derivative work under applicable law, the User
   hereby grants MultiPixel the same perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide,
   exclusive license rights described in Section 4 as a condition of using
   the Software’s API or interacting with the Software in any way.

d. Mods must not remove or alter copyright notices.

e. Users may not create, distribute, or use any software, tool, script,
   injector, loader, overlay, trainer, or other mechanism that interacts
   with, modifies, alters, hooks into, or manipulates the Software’s
   memory, process state, runtime behavior, or execution environment
   without explicit written approval from MultiPixel. This prohibition
   applies regardless of whether such software contains any MultiPixel
   code or is classified as a derivative work under applicable law.

4. Ownership of Mods

a. All Mods are derivative works of the Software.

b. By creating a Mod, the User grants MultiPixel a perpetual, irrevocable,
   worldwide, exclusive, transferable, sublicensable license to use,
   modify, adapt, reproduce, publish, distribute, and create derivative
   works from the Mod for any purpose, without compensation or additional
   permission.

c. The User retains authorship of their Mod where applicable, but agrees
   that MultiPixel’s licensed rights override any conflicting rights the
   User may hold.

d. The User waives any right to revoke or challenge this license, and
   waives any claim for compensation, attribution, or control over how the
   Mod is used by MultiPixel.

5. Mod Monetization

a. Monetization of Mods is prohibited unless explicitly approved.

b. If approved:
   i. MultiPixel receives fifteen percent (15%) of all gross revenue.
   ii. The creator must maintain accurate revenue records.
   iii. MultiPixel may request revenue reports at any time.
   iv. MultiPixel may revoke approval at any time.

c. MultiPixel may pursue legal action for unapproved monetization and may
   require the User to pay liquidated damages. Liquidated damages represent
   a reasonable pre-estimate of the harm caused by unauthorized commercial
   use of Mods and are owed immediately upon violation. These damages are
   compensatory, not punitive, and the User agrees they are fair and
   enforceable.If any liquidated damages amount is found by a court or 
   competent authority to be unenforceable, excessive, or invalid under 
   applicable law, the User agrees that MultiPixel shall instead be entitled 
   to recover the maximum amount permitted by law, including but not limited to 
   compensation for economic loss, breach of trust, brand dilution, administrative 
   burden, and the costs of enforcement.



6. Server Hosting

a. Users may operate Servers without approval ONLY IF:
   i. The Server is non-commercial (no revenue of any kind).
   ii. The Server does not involve banned topics (e.g., politics).

b. Servers require explicit written approval if:
   i. They generate revenue of any kind.
   ii. They involve political content.
   iii. They involve any restricted or sensitive topics.

c. Hosting any Server without required approval is a violation regardless of
   intent, testing status, or scale.

7. Server Monetization

a. Monetization requires explicit written approval.

b. If approved:
   i. MultiPixel receives thirty percent (30%) of all gross revenue.
   ii. Operators must maintain accurate revenue records.
   iii. MultiPixel may request revenue reports at any time.
   iv. MultiPixel may revoke approval at any time.

c. MultiPixel may pursue legal action for unapproved monetization and may
   require the Server operator to pay liquidated damages. Liquidated
   damages represent a reasonable pre-estimate of the harm caused by
   unauthorized commercial activity and are owed immediately upon breach.
   These damages are compensatory, not punitive, and the operator agrees
   they are fair and enforceable.


8. Political Servers

a. Political Servers require explicit written approval from MultiPixel.

b. Political Servers must be clearly labeled as such.

c. Political Servers may be official or unofficial.

d. MultiPixel retains full oversight and may:
   i. Impose additional rules.
   ii. Require moderation standards.
   iii. Require age restrictions.
   iv. Require transparency and logging.
   v. Revoke approval at any time.

e. Political content is prohibited on all non-political Servers.

9. Online Safety and Behavior

The following are strictly prohibited:

a. Harassment, bullying, hate speech, or targeted abuse.

b. Extremist, violent, or illegal content.

c. Adult content, sexual content, or grooming behavior.

d. Encouraging self-harm or dangerous acts.

e. Stalking, doxxing, or revealing private information.

10. Asset Protection

a. Users may not extract, export, scrape, or reuse any assets, including:
   textures, models, audio, animations, UI, maps, or other content.

b. Users may not reproduce, recreate, or adapt any MultiPixel assets,
   including textures, models, animations, audio, UI elements, or other
   protected expressions, for use in other games or engines. This
   restriction applies to specific expressions of the assets, not to
   general artistic style.

c. Users may not use any MultiPixel assets, source code, logic, algorithms,
   data structures, file formats, engine behavior, or any other component
   of the Software in any form of AI training, dataset creation, machine
   learning processing, embedding extraction, or generative model input.
   Users may not use the Software to fine‑tune, condition, guide, or
   otherwise influence any AI system, nor may they generate AI‑produced
   content that imitates, replicates, or derives from MultiPixel code,
   assets, or functionality.

d. Video content (gameplay, reviews, commentary, exposés) is allowed.

11. Client Modification Rules

a. Users may not:
   i. Create custom launchers.
   ii. Create custom clients.
   iii. Modify executable code.
   iv. Modify network packets.
   v. Reverse engineer protocols.
   vi. Use proxies to alter traffic.
   vii. Use packet sniffers or replay tools.
   viii. Use automation tools or bots.
   ix. Bypass anti-cheat or DRM.
   x. The Software may verify Mod approval status at runtime. Any Mod that lacks
   valid approval, signature, or authorization may be automatically blocked,
   disabled, or reported by the Software. Attempts to load unapproved Mods
   constitute a violation of this License.
   xi. Users may not attach, inject, hook, or interface any external process,
    library, or tool with the Software for the purpose of modifying,
    influencing, or observing its runtime behavior.

12. Server Data and Telemetry

a. MultiPixel may collect:
   i. Which Servers a player joins.
   ii. When they join.
   iii. Chat messages.
   iv. Usage data.

b. This data is used to optimize user experience and improve safety.

c. Approved Servers may collect:
   i. Join/leave logs.
   ii. Chat logs.

d. Servers may NOT collect:
   i. Personal data.
   ii. Payment information.
   iii. Sensitive data.

13. Mod Quality and Safety

a. Mods must not:
   i. Break the Software.
   ii. Introduce vulnerabilities.
   iii. Interfere with anti-cheat.
   iv. Modify executable code.
   v. Modify network packets.
   vi. Harm performance.
   vii. Contain malware or harmful code.

14. Server Monetization Rules

Allowed:
a. Lootboxes.
b. In-game currency.
c. Roles (VIP, cosmetic ranks).

Prohibited:
d. Gambling.
e. Crypto/NFTs.
f. Selling progression.
g. Selling admin/mod roles.
h. Pay-to-win mechanics (unless approved).

15. Enforcement Tools

MultiPixel reserves the right to:

a. Audit Server revenue.
b. Audit Mod revenue.

c. Require the User to pay liquidated damages for violations involving
   unauthorized monetization, unauthorized Server operation, or any other
   prohibited commercial activity. Liquidated damages are calculated as
   follows:

      i. For revenue-based violations: liquidated damages equal three (3)
         times the unpaid revenue share owed to MultiPixel, or the
         documented fair market value of the transaction, whichever is
         greater.

     ii. For non-revenue commercial violations: liquidated damages equal a
         fixed amount defined per violation category in the Governance
         Framework, not to exceed a reasonable estimate of the harm caused.

    iii. These liquidated damages represent a reasonable pre-estimate of
         the harm caused by such violations and are compensatory, not
         punitive. The User agrees they are fair, enforceable, and owed
         immediately upon breach.


d. Pursue legal action.
e. Revoke approvals.
f. Ban Servers.
g. Issue cease-and-desist orders.
h. Block IPs or accounts.
i. Enforce DMCA.
j. Terminate licenses instantly.

16. Branding and Presentation

a. Unofficial Servers must display “Unofficial Server”.

b. Unofficial Mods must display “Unofficial Mod”.

c. Users may not use the names:
   “Raptor4”, “Raptor4mc”, “MultiPixel”, or “Relimintor”
   in:
   i. domain names,
   ii. social media handles,
   iii. server names,
   iv. community names,
   without explicit approval.

d. Users may not use MultiPixel logos without approval.

e. Users may not claim official partnership without approval.

